<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FFA1FFDD39D30F7F4320BE39" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FFA1FFDD39D30F7F4320BE39" blockId="47.[136,1452,1096,1303]" pageId="47" pageNumber="274">
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA1FFDD39D30F7F4688BF4D" authority="Arruda" authorityName="Arruda (Koster" authorityYear="1816" box="[136,422,1096,1122]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virginalis">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA1FFDD39D30F7F467FBF4D" box="[136,337,1096,1122]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="274">Mimosa virginalis</emphasis>
Arruda
</taxonomicName>
was cited by 
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FFA1FFDD3B630F7F45FDBF4C" author="Koster, H." box="[568,723,1096,1123]" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" refId="ref42743" refString="Koster, H. (1816) Travels in Brazil. Longman, Hurst, Rees, Orme and Brown, London, 501 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 60564" type="book" year="1816">Koster (1816)</bibRefCitation>
in a brief comment about the medicinal use of the plant, especially regarding its astringent properties, without mentioning any of its morphological characteristics or anything that can be interpreted as a diagnosis. There is no intention of the author in treating the plant as a new species, or as a species distinct from the remaining 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA1FFDD38930F83450CBFE1" box="[456,546,1205,1230]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA1FFDD38930F83450CBFE1" box="[456,546,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="274">Mimosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FFA1FFDD3B950F8244C4BFE0" author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[718,1002,1204,1231]" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" refId="ref44802" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976) Taxonomic Literature. A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types. Vol. 1 A-G. 2 nd. ed. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht, 1136 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48631" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, the nomenclatural 
<typeStatus id="7C4B50F0FFA1FFDD3D900F834228BFE0" box="[1227,1286,1205,1231]" pageId="47" pageNumber="274">types</typeStatus>
of the species described by Arruda da Câmara are unknown, thus it is not possible to confirm the identity of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA1FFDD3D8D0FEF428ABFDD" authorityName="Arruda (Koster" authorityYear="1816" box="[1238,1444,1240,1266]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virginalis">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA1FFDD3D8D0FEF428ABFDD" box="[1238,1444,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="274">Mimosa virginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, neither as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA1FFDD38C00FCA45C8BE39" box="[411,742,1276,1302]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adstringens">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA1FFDD38C00FCA45C8BE39" box="[411,742,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="274">Stryphnodendron adstringens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as frequently recognized.
</paragraph>
